Algorithm: Generational Garbage Collection

Key Insight: Young → Old promotion reduces collection frequency

REGIONS:
├─ Young Gen: Eden + Survivor0 + Survivor1
├─ Old Gen: Long-lived objects
└─ Age = generation count survived

MINOR GC (Collect Young Only):
────────────────────────────
minorGC()
  // Collect only young generation

  live_objects = {}

  // 1. Mark phase (roots + remembered set)
  for each root in STACK_ROOTS:
    mark(root)
  for each old→young ref in REMEMBERED_SET:
    mark(young_object)

  // 2. Copy survivors to next survivor space
  for each live object in young_gen:
    if obj.age > PROMOTION_THRESHOLD:
      copy_to_old_gen(obj)
      obj.age = old_gen_age
    else:
      copy_to_survivor(obj)
      obj.age++

  // 3. Clear Eden and swap survivor spaces
  clear_eden()
  swap_survivor_spaces()

TIME: O(young_gen_size) - much faster!


MAJOR GC (Collect All):
──────────────────────
majorGC()
  // Full heap collection (fallback)

  // 1. Mark from all roots
  for each root in ALL_ROOTS:
    mark(root)

  // 2. Sweep both young and old
  sweep_young_gen()
  sweep_old_gen()

  // 3. Compact both generations
  compact_young_gen()
  compact_old_gen()

TIME: O(heap_size) - slow!


COLLECTION SCHEDULING:
──────────────────────
monitor heap usage:

  if eden_full:
    minorGC()  // ~10-100ms pause

  if old_gen_usage > threshold:
    majorGC()  // ~1-10 seconds pause (EXPENSIVE!)

  if metaspace_full:
    collect_metaspace()  // Unload dead classes

STATISTICS TYPICAL APPLICATION:
├─ Minor GC: every 1-2 seconds, 50ms pause
├─ Major GC: once per day, 5 second pause
├─ Frequency ratio: 1000:1 (1000 minors per 1 major)
└─ 99% of garbage collected in minor GC